Parser - Class in parser
Objects of the class Parser use the scanner.Scanner object to read and tokenize a string of inputs, then evaluates statements, expressions, terms, and factors in increasing levels of priority, according to the order of operations.

Constructor for objects of class Parser
ParserTest - Class in parser
Class ParserTest reads in a file and uses a Parser object (from the package parser) to evaluate the input, a piece of Pascal code consisting of BEGIN/END block statements, variable declarations, print statements, arithmetic operations using +, -, *, /, and (), IF/THEN/ELSE statements, and WHILE loops.
